definition.value: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as arachidonoyl
Any polyunsaturated fatty acid containing 22 carbons and 2 double bonds
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as oleoyl.
A docosadienoic acid having two cis-double bonds at position 13 and 16 respectively.
A 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as oleoyl.
A lysophosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1-(10Z)-heptadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol.
1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the 1-acyl group is specified as (10Z)-heptadecenoyl.
An octadecenoyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (11Z)-octadecenoyl-CoA.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-oleoyl-2-(11Z)-octadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.
An octadecenoyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (6E)-octadecenoyl-CoA.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-oleoyl-2-(6Z)-octadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.
A fatty amide resulting from the formal condensation of palmitic acid with the primary amino group of 2-amino-3-(morpholin-4-yl)-1-phenylpropan-1-ol.
An N-[1-hydroxy-3-(morpholin-4-yl)-1-phenylpropan-2-yl]hexadecanamide in which both stereocentres have R configuration.
A galactosyl group derived from the disaccharide alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)-D-galactose. Implied reactive epitope within gangliosides LM1, GD1a and GT1b.
A galactosyl group derived from the disaccharide alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->6)-D-galactose.
A flavone C-glycoside that is  apigenin attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl and a beta-L-arabinopyranosyl residues at positions 6 and 8 respectively via C-glycosidic linkage.
A sialosyl group derived from the disaccharide alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminic acid.
An N-[1-hydroxy-3-(morpholin-4-yl)-1-phenylpropan-2-yl]hexadecanamide in which both stereocentres have S configuration.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (1R,2R)- and (1S,2S)-1-phenyl-2-palmitoylamino-3-morpholino-1-propanol.
A sialosyl group derived from N-acetylneuraminic acid.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and icosanoyl (arachidoyl) respectively.

A single-strand DNA oligonucleotide comprised of four deoxyadenosine, two deoxycytidine, four thymidine and eight deoxyguanidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence G-C-G-A-G-T-G-A-T-T-A-T-G-G-A-C-G-G, with a (6-4) lesion at the central two thymidine residues (PDB entry: 3VW3).
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of both free phosphate OH groups of any 2,2'-dilysocardiolipin.
A 2-monolysocardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both free phosphate OH groups of 2-oleoyl-2'-monolysocardiolipin.

A  quaternary ammonium ion comprising an anilinium ion core having three methyl substituents on the aniline nitrogen, and a 3-[(dimethylcarbamoyl)oxy] substituent at position 3. It is a parasympathomimetic which acts as a reversible acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.
A cardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both free phosphate OH groups of 2'-oleoylcardiolipin.
A 1-acyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as arachidonoyl.

A tripeptide that is L-leucyl-L-leucyl-L-leucine in which the C-terminal carboxy group has been reduced to the corresponding aldehyde and the N-terminal amino group is protected as its benzyloxycarbonyl derivative.
A secondary amino compound that is tyramine in which the hydrogen of the phenolic hydroxy group has been replaced by a methyl group.
A monocarboxylic acid amide that is lactic acid in which the carboxylic acid group has been converted to the corresponding carboxamide.
An alpha-amino fatty acid that is caprylic acid which is substituted at position 2 by an amino group.
A dicarboxylic acid monoester that is succinic acid in which one of the carboxy groups has been converted to its methyl ester.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the 2-acyl substituent is specified as oleoyl.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl substituent is specified as oleoyl.
A ketohexose monophosphate that is 3-dehydro-D-glucose having the monophosphate group located at position 6.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group of any 1-(alk-1-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group of any 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine.
An oligonucleotide that is a fragment of a larger single-stranded DNA molecule (either naturally occurring or synthetic). Phosphono groups may or may not be present at the 3'- and 5'- termini.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-) in which the 2-acyl substituent is specified as oleoyl.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the 2-acyl substituent is specified as arachidonoyl.

A single-strand DNA oligonucleotide comprised of four deoxyadenosine, eight deoxycytidine, four thymidine and two deoxyguanidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-C-C-G-T-C-C-A-T-A-A-T-C-A-C-T-C-G. (PDB entry: 3VW3).
A single-strand DNA oligonucleotide consisting of a thymidine residue phospho-linked 3'->5' to a deoxycytidine residue (PDB entry: 2OK0).
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl); major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylinositol 28:0 in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) and lauroyl (dodecanoyl) respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as myristoyl and oleoyl respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
A trimethoxyflavone that is quercetagetin methylated at positions 4', 6 and 7.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which both acyl groups are specified as oleoyl.
